\ ask-claude.h2o — ask Claude twenty questions concurrently via lib/claude,
\ five requests in flight at a time, then report the session's total cost.
\ exercises: lib/claude (request-body, user-message, build-curl-argv,
\ extract-response, response-cost), parallel-run, and dimensioned ¢ arithmetic.
\
\ Needs ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in the environment and curl on the PATH.

"lib/claude.h2o" load

"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001" to claude-model
256 to claude-max-tokens

\ Twenty short questions.
[ "In one sentence, what is a stack-based programming language?"
  "In one sentence, what is tail-call optimization?"
  "In one sentence, what is a continuation?"
  "In one sentence, what is NaN-boxing?"
  "In one sentence, what is a mark-sweep garbage collector?"
  "In one sentence, what does the Forth word DOES> do?"
  "In one sentence, what is a delimited continuation?"
  "In one sentence, how does an interpreter differ from a compiler?"
  "In one sentence, what is direct threading in an interpreter?"
  "In one sentence, what is a coroutine?"
  "In one sentence, what is referential transparency?"
  "In one sentence, how does a hash table work?"
  "In one sentence, what is the actor model of concurrency?"
  "In one sentence, what is copy-on-write?"
  "In one sentence, what is a regular expression?"
  "In one sentence, how does a process differ from a thread?"
  "In one sentence, what is a closure?"
  "In one sentence, what is memoization?"
  "In one sentence, what is a finite state machine?"
  "In one sentence, what is Unicode normalization?" ] to questions

\ One curl argv per question, built with lib/claude; run five at a time.
questions [: |> question | [ question user-message ] request-body build-curl-argv :] map
  5 parallel-run to results

\ Print each question with its answer.
[: |> idx |
  "Q: " . questions idx @i . cr
  "A: " . results idx @i extract-response . cr
  cr
:] questions size i-times

\ Total cost of the session: sum response-cost over every successful result.
results 0 ¢ [: |> total result |
  result :status @ 0 = if total result response-cost + else total then
:] reduce
"Total cost: " . . cr

bye
